FAQs
What are the top universities to study dentistry in Spain?

The University of Barcelona, Complutense University of Madrid, and University of Valencia are among the top universities for dentistry in Spain.
Do I need to know Spanish while study in Spain?

Most dental programs in Spain are taught in Spanish, so proficiency in the language is typically required. Some universities offer English-taught programs.
What documents are needed to apply for a dental program in Spain?

You will need academic transcripts, proof of Spanish language proficiency, letters of recommendation, a personal statement, a valid passport, and passport-sized photographs.
